channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Trump Endorses Sam Brown in Nevada’s Key Senate Race
item.description: Mr. Brown, a former Army captain, is the leading candidate in a crowded field of Republicans vying to take on Senator Jacky Rosen, a vulnerable Democratic incumbent in a presidential battleground.

item.title: E.U. Parliament Election Updates: Live Results
item.description: See totals and national results from the 2024 E.U. parliament elections.

item.title: Volvo is moving EV production from China to Belgium as the EU eyes tariffs on Beijing
item.description: On top of transferring production of Volvo’s EX30 and EX90 models to Belgium, the carmaker may also move assembly of some Volvo models bound for the UK.

item.title: India-Pakistan Cricket World Cup Match Brings 34,000 Fans to Long Island
item.description: Security was tight, but the mood was jubilant in the temporary stadium in Nassau County, where India won 119-113 in a highly anticipated showdown.

item.title: In E.U. Elections, the Center Holds, but the Far Right Still Wreaks Havoc
item.description: Voters in the European Union delivered strong gains to anti-immigrant, nationalist parties, challenging leaders in Germany and France, and unsettling the political establishment.

item.title: Benny Gantz quits Israel’s government, saying Netanyahu is preventing a ‘true victory’ over Hamas
item.description: Far-right party leader Itamar Ben Gvir demanded to be added to the war cabinet in Gantz’s place.

item.title: In Las Vegas, Trump Appeals to Local Workers and Avoids Talk of Conviction
item.description: At a rally on Sunday, former President Donald J. Trump promised to end taxes on tips for hospitality workers in a speech otherwise filled with familiar refrains.

item.title: Middle East Crisis: Benny Gantz Quits Israel’s Emergency Government in Dispute Over Gaza
item.description: The move is unlikely to force Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu from office. But Mr. Gantz’s exit exposes the fractures within Israel’s leadership eight months into the war in Gaza.

item.title: Donald Trump will be interviewed by probation officials ahead of his sentencing for N.Y. felony convictions
item.description: Trump will do the interview via a computer video conference from his residence at the Mar-a-Lago club in Palm Beach, Florida.

item.title: In E.U. Elections, the Center Holds, but the Far Right Still Wreaks Havoc
item.description: Voters in the European Union delivered strong gains to anti-immigrant, nationalist parties, challenging leaders in Germany and France, and unsettling the political establishment.

item.title: The Other War: How Israel Scours Gaza for Clues About the Hostages
item.description: The rescue of four Israelis in Gaza in a ferocious assault over the weekend offered a glimpse into an ambitious intelligence operation aimed at bringing home those held by Hamas.

item.title: Far-right parties make stunning gains in EU election, prompting Macron to call snap vote in France
item.description: The long-established Social Democratic party also fell behind the extreme-right Alternative for Germany.

item.title: Israel’s Euphoria Over Hostage Rescue May Be Fleeting
item.description: The operation conducted by Israel’s military to free four hostages resulted in a high death toll among Palestinians and has not resolved the challenges facing the Israeli government.

item.title: 'Bond King' Bill Gross is about to make a killing on his stamp collection, but he thinks the market is due for a correction and is getting out
item.description: The Robert A. Siegel auction house said "this collection promises to set a new high-water mark for stamp collecting when it crosses the auction block."
